<ProsePage
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How the OpenData website handles data. Short version: no accounts, no personal data required, aggregate analytics only."
  label="Legal"
  updated="July 1, 2026"
>
  <p>
    OpenData is open-source software you run on your own infrastructure. This
    policy covers only the website at <b>opendata.dev</b> and its documentation.
    It does not cover software you download and self-host — that runs entirely on
    your systems, and we never see its data.
  </p>

  <h2>No accounts, no personal data</h2>
  <p>
    You do not create an account or provide any personal information to use this
    site, read the docs, or download the software. We do not ask for, collect, or
    store names, email addresses, or payment details.
  </p>

  <h2>Analytics</h2>
  <p>
    We measure aggregate traffic — page views and referrers — to understand
    what's useful, using Vercel Web Analytics (which does not use cookies and does
    not track you across sites) and Google Tag Manager. This data is aggregate and
    not used to identify individuals. We do not sell it or use it for advertising.
  </p>

  <h2>Third-party links</h2>
  <p>
    The site links to services with their own privacy policies, including GitHub,
    Discord, and our documentation host. When you follow those links, their
    policies apply.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>
    We'll update this page if our practices change and revise the date above.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about privacy? Reach us through any of the channels on our
    <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
  </p>
</ProsePage>
